Cheesecake is not a dessert one finds in Holland often. I had not enjoyed a slice in a couple of years, and after seeing Nigella on BBC making a cheesecake I had a craving for this delicacy. I chose this recipe for a dinner I was having for my in-laws. The recipe was easy to make the night before and it turned out delish. I did have to tweek some of the amounts, as other cooks have stated. I used the juice of one whole large lemon, and also used the whole zest of that lemon. I baked in a convection oven, so the temp used was 170C/340F for 1 hour, I then turned the oven down to 140C/285F for 20 minutes longer. I used a raspberry coulis (recipe found on this site)thickened with a cornstarch slurry as the topping with fresh raspberries as garnish. The dessert was fantastic and a good success, as it pleased all the Dutchies at the table. The recipe is a definite keeper! I will definitely make it again.

