This cheesecake is phenomenal. I made it for a July 4th BBQ and it was a hit! Someone I didn't know actually came up and kissed me on the cheek in a fit of cheesecake-induced ecstasy. I used the large "brownie size" rectangle glass baking dish - doubled the crust but not the filling, which ended up being a perfect amount. Used pecan sandies as per a previous reviewer's suggestion (yum!) and the juice from 2 whole lemons. Somehow it took nearly 2 hours to bake. I got nervous, finally decided it was done when the top was an even shade of gold and I could poke it in the middle and encounter a little bit of resistance, while overall it still had some wiggle. It turned out perfectly - "fluffy", rich, lemony and delicious - but the crust stuck to the glass dish despite greasing it first.. so if you take the baking dish route, lining with foil and lifting it out is probably the way to go. Served with blackberry & blueberry coulis on the side. The kind of cheesecake that might change your life.

