UNBELIEVABLE! I made this cheesecake yesterday and it was outstanding. I took the advice of those who had reviewed it and doubled the amount of shortbread to 1 cup, added and additional 4T of lemon juice, as 2T would never have been enough. Additionallly, I had to bake it almost 2 hours. I started it in a conventional oven and baked it for the last 30 minutes in a convection oven with a piece of that new Reynolds Release foil on top to prevent it from becoming too brown. I served it with fresh whipped cream, although raspberry coulis would be great too. This cheesecake was absolutely a hit. And, I don't bake! Cooking I love, but baking is such a chore to me. In fact, my repitoire of desserts usually consists of Tart Tatin, because I really don't like to bake. I will make this again and again!

