Rating: 4
I've made this cheesecake three times now - every time to rave reviews from my cheesecake audience. I've made it with and without the "notorious" marscapone cheese and, although expensive, I believe that the marscapone adds a richness & smoothness to the cake that makes it worth the expense. The crust recipe should definitely be doubled, but I'm having a hard time finding the perfect balance between butter & flour & cookie crumbs. You definitely do not need to double the butter, but if someone could reply with a more exact way to make enough of the crust, I'd really appreciate it. Enjoy!!

Rating: 3
I followed the suggestions to add more lemon. I added 5 T. of fresh lemon juice, 2 tsp. of fresh lemon zest, and 1 tsp. of lemon oil (concentrate from the zest)--PERFECT. Plus I added 2 tablespoons of poppyseeds for color & crunch--GREAT! For the crust, I added more shortbread cookies to suck up the excess butter that people commented on--plus I like crust, but in this case too much crust disturbs the balance. Next time I will stick to the creator's intent and have just a thin layer of crust on the bottom because the crust is very sweet (the cookies are full of sugar PLUS you add even more sugar which [gasp] isn't really necessary). The cheesecake itself is the sweetest I've ever tasted (I've used at least 15 other recipes but the sugar in this one STANDS OUT for some odd reason) so crust up the pans sides is overkill (for the 5 people in my group). The cake itself has a truly wonderful, dense texture (not for those that like light & airy cheesecakes). I used the water bath with no problem.

