As often is the case, using the reader's suggestions made this a better recipe than following the recipe as written. I don't see the point of grinding up cookies as part of the crust. Any basic shortbread recipe creates the same impact. I too doubled the lemon and the zest. A very nice lemon flavor. I also glazed the top with 1/2c sour cream & 1/4c sugar mixture 10 minutes before the cake was done. If I would have followed the recommended 1 hour cooking time, I would have had a cake too soft to cut. 1 hr 20 min to 1 hr 30 min was closer to accurate. Overall, with modifications, this is an excellent summer cheesecake recipe, tasting much lighter than it actually is. The shortbread is a nice flavor combination with the lemon. Definately a keeper!

