Rating: 4
Wonderful for those who prefer creamy cheesecake! I added extra zest (about 1 T total) and used 4 oz cream cheese and 1/2 cup sour cream in place of the mascarpone. (I used Philadelphia cream cheese). I had grave doubts about the crust recipe when I realized how much butter was in it. But I only added 4 extra Lorna Doone cookies after increasing the recipe by half. After baking the crust was saturated and there was a little oil in the foil around the pan. Unbelievably, the crust came out crisp and was really outstanding. I decorated the cake with fresh raspberry coulis in a deep pool on top, fresh raspberries heaped over and a little coulis on them for color and shine, and a frosting of cream cheese, a little butter, sour cream and confectioner's sugar applied with a decorating tube in a continuing scroll around the edge of the cake. The cake was so evenly brown and neat-looking right out of the oven, though, that I was tempted to serve it completely plain. It was greatly appreciated. The lemony flavor of the cake, the buttery, crisp crust, the tart-sweet coulis, and the texture of the raspberries were right on.

