This was so delicious, I made 2 of them over the weekend (when I went home for my mom's birthday). However, I modified the recipe a little. No mascarpone cheese in rural towns, so added one more package of cream cheese for a total of 5 8-oz packages of cream cheese. Crushed one and a half packages of Keebler Shortbread cookies and slightly increased other crust ingredients to compensate for the additional crumbs, we like thick crusts. Also, increased fresh squeezed lemon juice to about 5 or 6 tablespoons and added 1 heaping tablespoon of vanilla. Baked in a 10-inch pan, at a little lower than 350 degrees, and a little longer. Unbelievable, smooth, creamy lemony taste with wonderful, thick(er) shortbread crust. Will make again, and again.

